151.22. Erechtheus according to the story perished in the war against the inhabitants of Eleusis under Eumolpus, after he had slain the latter. For this reason Cotta here couples his name with that of Codrus who lilrewise died for his country. Erechtbus was originally a surname of Poseidon, like AEgeus; it was also perpetuated in the public worship in the title Ποσειδῶν Ἐρεχθεὺς.
